CHAPTER LXI.

The Senate determines not to ransom the captives. The delegate who had returned into Hannibal's camp under a. false pretext, remains in Rome as if ho had fulfilled his oath. The senate order him to be- given up to Hannibal. Another account. respecting the delegatos. Defection of numerous allies. No mention, however, made of peace. On Varro’s return to the city men of ull ranks go out to meet him, and thanks are given him for not having despaired of the State.— 13.c. 216.
